the end of the North Korean Kim Dynasty, or so said one half of the duo named HaYoon. The other half of HaYoon laughed uncontrollably at her statement. It seemed that the 5 year war against the North Koreans that the South Koreans went through has yet to be completely forgotten.

“N? Are you kidding me? Of course that’s not the most significant event in the past 5 years. Most South Koreans would laugh at what you said. It has been 30 years since the 3rd World War and the world has been playing nice for the past 20 years. There has been absolutely no hatred or rivalry between any two nations. South Korea and North Korea live together in peace. North Korea is like China. Superpower if you will.”

I immediately stopped writing in my journal at that point. The sheer negative tone in which I had written for the first 3 paragraphs immediately switched to a positive one. 30 years ago, South Korea joined the World Alliance in order to defeat North Korea, China, and of course Pakistan by default. At the time, there were only three superpowers on the planet known as ‘The Alliance’, ‘The Revolutionary Nation’ and of course Pakistan. The Alliance was the strongest superpower, making up half the world’s military power. Revolutionary Nation consisted of the West. They represented liberalism and were the weakest superpower.
